  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Note: following regulatory clearance, the indicated patient population was extended to include paediatric patients (body surface area 0.5–1.0 m²) operating at reduced flow rates (1.2–2.0 L/min), a sub-range not represented in the original validation campaign. The assessment team concluded that the existing validation evidence, which covered adult flow rates of 2.5–6.0 L/min, provides sufficient coverage by extrapolation of the validated turbulence and shear-stress correlations. No new experimental validation results were commissioned for the expanded paediatric envelope.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
