      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validated QoIs (RH index, wall shear stress distribution) are directly used in the regulatory decision. QoI relevance score meets level 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index is the primary regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Wall shear stress is the mechanistic driver in the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model. Both QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision. Relevance level 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on the same pump geometry and fluid system as the COU. Operating conditions span the intended use envelope or are demonstrably bounding.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry identical to the production model geometry. Fluid system and hemolysis model are consistent. Adult flow range (2.5–6.0 L/min) validated; the assessment team asserts the validated range is bounding for the paediatric sub-range (1.2–2.0 L/min) because shear-stress scaling with flow rate is monotonic and the power-law hemolysis model was calibrated on the higher-stress adult regime. No experimental data points within the paediatric flow range are included in the validation dataset. Relevance level 2 is claimed on the basis of physical similarity arguments."
    },
    {
