      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence of residuals below 1×10⁻⁵ for continuity and momentum equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%.",
      "rationale": "All production simulations converged to residuals below 1×10⁻⁵. Mass imbalance consistently below 0.005%. Solver error level 1 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary condition application and material property assignment verified against test report.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup performed by a second analyst not involved in model construction. Boundary conditions, turbulence model settings, and hemolysis model coefficients verified against TR-2022-04. Use error level 1 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified against benchmark data; hemolysis power-law model applicability documented for the flow regime of interest.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model validated against PIV benchmark (ValidationResult morrison-vr-03) showing 8% RMS velocity agreement. Giersiepen hemolysis power-law model is the standard for CFD hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps per published literature. Model form level 2 satisfied for the adult regime; the assessment team notes the model was not independently validated at the lower Reynolds numbers characteristic of paediatric flows but considers the functional form applicable by continuity of the governing physics."
    },
